Since the release of the [[Radeon R600#Radeon HD 3800|Radeon HD 3000 series]] products, [[ATI Video Card Suffixes|previous PRO, XT, GT, and XTX suffixes]] were eliminated, products will be differentiated by changing the last two digits of the product model number (for instance, HD 3850 and HD 3870, giving the impression that the HD 3870 model having higher performance than HD 3850).<ref name="vrzone-071017">{{cite web | url=http://www.vr-zone.com/articles/RV670_is_Radeon_HD_3800_Series/5358.html#Scene_1 | title=RV670 is Radeon HD 3800 Series | publisher=VR-Zone | date=October 17, 2007}}</ref> Similar changes to the IGP naming were spotted as well, for the previously launched [[AMD 690 chipset series#M690T|AMD M690T chipset]] with side-port memory, the IGP is named "Radeon X1270", while for the [[AMD 690 chipset series#690G|AMD 690G chipset]], the IGP is named "Radeon X1250", as for [[AMD 690 chipset series#690V|AMD 690V chipset]], the IGP is clocked lower and having fewer functions and thus named "Radeon X1200". The new numbering scheme of video products are shown below:

